27/04/2010
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- High Representative Valentin Inzko met on Monday (April 26th) visiting UN war crimes tribunal chief prosecutor Serge Brammertz. The Office of the High Representative issued a statement, saying Inzko reiterated that Western Balkan countries are willing to resolve all issues related to crimes committed during the 1990s' conflicts. He added that lasting peace will be guaranteed through investigating war crimes and bringing those responsible to justice. (Dnevnik.ba, Fena, OHR - 26/04/10)
